  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Bug Net</b> is a <linked>tool</linked> used to capture certain <linked>critters</linked> as <linked>inventory</linked> items. It is swung like a <linked>broadsword</linked>, but it deals no damage. The Bug Net is nearly required in order to go <linked>fishing</linked>, as it is the initial and primary method of obtaining <linked>bait</linked>. Most critters that are insects, <linked>worms</linked>, or <linked>snails</linked> can function as bait once captured.",
    "The Bug Net is purchased from the <linked>Merchant</linked> for <span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span> <span class=\"coin\" title=\"25 Silver Coins\" data-sort-value=\"2500\"><span class=\"sc\">25<i> SC</i></span></span> / <span class=\"eico i3 i5\" title=\"Old-gen console and 3DS versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Old-gen console and 3DS versions)</span></span> <span class=\"coin\" title=\"1 Gold Coin\" data-sort-value=\"10000\"><span class=\"gc\">1<i> GC</i></span></span>.",
    "The <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Lavaproof Bug Net</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span></span> and <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Golden Bug Net</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span></span> are upgraded versions that are bigger, swing faster, and can destroy tall grass, vines, and uproot plants just like swords and other weapons do, despite dealing no damage. They are also able to catch <linked>Underworld</linked> critters, unlike the standard Bug Net; attempting to catch one with a standard Bug Net will set the player <linked>on fire</linked>."
